field1:{"type":"field","size":[248,241],"pos":[254,47],"locked":1,"border":0,"value":".jhf files are a common text format for representing Hershey fonts.\n\nEach line of the file consists of four fixed-width fields (id, length, left, right) followed by a sequence of (x,y) points making up the vertices of a series of polylines which make up a glyph, each delimited by the pair of characters \" R\" (a space followed by a capital R).\n\n\n\n\nthe left/right field and each of the pairs of characters making up a point are encoded as ASCII characters. Subtracting 'R' from the character gives its integral value: R is 0, Q is -1, T is +2, and so on.\n\nWell-formed .jhf files should not contain newlines within glyphs or non-displayable ASCII characters. The \"id\" field should correspond to a DeckRoman character index. .jhf files you find online may be malformed, but this is easy to correct by hand once you understand their structure."}
grid1:{"type":"grid","size":[233,90],"pos":[10,64],"locked":1,"scrollbar":0,"widths":[39,35],"value":{"name":["id    ","length","left  ","right ","points"],"length":["5","3","1","1","n"],"description":["decimal id of glyph","decimal number of points","left offset of bounding box","right offset of bounding box","a list of points"]}}
field2:{"type":"field","size":[233,17],"pos":[10,44],"locked":1,"font":"menu","border":0,"align":"center","value":"glyph fields"}
field3:{"type":"field","size":[233,17],"pos":[10,159],"locked":1,"font":"menu","border":0,"align":"center","value":"point encoding"}
grid2:{"type":"grid","size":[233,31],"pos":[10,178],"locked":1,"scrollbar":0,"lines":1,"value":{"...":["..."],"O":["-3"],"P":["-2"],"Q":["-1"],"R":["0"],"S":["+1"],"T":["+2"],"U":["+3"],"... ":["..."]}}
field4:{"type":"field","size":[100,16],"pos":[79,244],"locked":1,"border":0,"align":"center","value":{"text":["( ","see also"," )"],"font":["","",""],"arg":["","https://wiki.xxiivv.com/site/hershey.html",""]}}

