field1:{"type":"field","size":[228,241],"pos":[274,47],"locked":1,"border":0,"value":"The hershey.parse[] function takes a string in the .jhf format and returns a \"font\" that can be used by various other functions in the hershey module.\n\nA \"font\" in this context is a Lil dictionary that contains all the strokes of each glyph as well as some extra computed metadata like the maximum height of any glyph. Fonts can be losslessly encoded as LOVE data."}
