field1:{"type":"field","size":[209,106],"pos":[293,48],"locked":1,"border":0,"value":"To rotate a path, we can use Lil's polar/cartesian conversion operators, which are already perfectly suited to manipulating lists-of-lists-of-pairs:\n\n\"mag\" gives the distance to each point.\n\"heading\" gives the angle toward each point.\n\"unit\" gives points facing toward given angles at distance 1 (unit vectors)."}
ex1:{"type":"field","size":[276,254],"pos":[10,48],"border":1,"scrollbar":1,"style":"code","value":"p:hershey.textpath[hf_futura \"Text\"]\nc.clear[]\n\non path_trans delta x do\n x+list list delta\nend\n\non path_rot angle x do\n (mag x)*unit angle+heading x\nend\n\nnp: path_trans[80,10 path_rot[pi/4 p]]\nc.line @ np"}
