field1:{"type":"field","size":[209,106],"pos":[293,48],"locked":1,"border":0,"value":"A variety of nonlinear squashing and stretching effects on paths are possible by using the \"mag\" operator to measure the distance of every point from the origin and blending the result into the scale, rotation, or translation of each point individually. As with the other effects we've discussed, this can be accomplished without writing any explicit loops."}
ex1:{"type":"field","size":[276,254],"pos":[10,48],"border":1,"scrollbar":1,"style":"code","value":"p:hershey.textpathc[\n hf_futura\n \"Distortion\" c.size\n]\nc.clear[]\n\n\n# center at origin\np:p-list list c.size/2\n\n# non-uniform scale,\n# with sinusoidal animation\np:p*.3+(mag p)*(.02*1+sin sys.frame/30)\n\n# re-center on canvas\np:p+list list c.size/2\n\n\nc.line @ p\n"}
